From: Kyle Orciuch <kyle@edgetrace.ai>
Date: Sun, 15 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH 1/3] dkms.conf: fix module array gaps when ov05c10 is skipped

AlmaLinux 10.1 (kernel 6.12) does not ship CONFIG_V4L2_CCI_I2C, so the
ov05c10 conditional block is skipped.  The original file used static
indices [0]..[21]; skipping ov05c10 left a gap (e.g. nothing at [6])
which caused DKMS to silently drop all subsequent modules.

Replace the static index literals with a $_idx counter incremented by
((_idx++)) after each entry so indices are always contiguous regardless
of which conditional branches are taken.

Also tighten the ov05c10 block: check CONFIG_V4L2_CCI_I2C in
/boot/config-${kernelver} before registering the module, in addition to
the existing kernel-version guard.

Signed-off-by: Kyle Orciuch <kyle@edgetrace.ai>
---
 dkms.conf | 143 +++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++-----------
 1 file changed, 113 insertions(+), 30 deletions(-)

diff --git a/dkms.conf b/dkms.conf
index d9667cb10..37e9b5591 100644
--- a/dkms.conf
+++ b/dkms.conf
@@ -40,113 +40,143 @@ KV_IPU6_ISYS=6.10.0
 KV_IMX471=6.10.0
 KV_S5K3J1=6.10.0

-BUILT_MODULE_NAME[0]="hm11b1"
-BUILT_MODULE_LOCATION[0]="drivers/media/i2c"
-DEST_MODULE_LOCATION[0]="/updates"
-
-BUILT_MODULE_NAME[1]="ov01a1s"
